<article id="post-575" class="post-575 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains category-travel tag-around-the-world tag-china tag-hong-kong">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/06/going-uphill-to-victoria-peak/" rel="bookmark">Going uphill to Victoria Peak</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>After meeting up with Amy, following our mutual attire sizings (and having a snack in a very Irish bar, oddly sitting amidst a lot of very Chinese surroundings), we took a ride up the Victora Peak Tram.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/06/going-uphill-to-victoria-peak/#more-575" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Going uphill to Victoria Peak&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

