<article id="post-552" class="post-552 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains category-travel tag-around-the-world tag-beijing tag-china">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/ni-hao-beijing/" rel="bookmark">Ni hao, Beijing!</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I woke up at the Datong station. I&#8217;d slept about seven hours, but decided that I wasn&#8217;t going to miss crossing this part of China. I was in a new country, and be darned if I&#8217;m not going to witness this!<br />
<a><img src="http://www.howtogetlost.com/media/DSC03621.JPG" alt="Datong station" width="300" /></a><br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/05/ni-hao-beijing/#more-552" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Ni hao, Beijing!&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
