<article id="post-381" class="post-381 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains category-travel tag-british-columbia tag-fairmont-hot-springs tag-museums">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/09/bc-vacation-fort-steele-cranbrook/" rel="bookmark">BC Vacation: Fort Steele and Cranbrook</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>No-one told me that we were doing any surprises this weekend. &#8216;Course, then it wouldn&#8217;t be a surprise, would it?<br />
Allen (Alex&#8217;s father) took Jean (Alex&#8217;s stepmom) down to Cranbrook so she could catch a flight out to southern Ontario for a wedding. This meant the condo was quiet for a number of hours. That meant we didn&#8217;t get up until late. I love sleeping in.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/09/bc-vacation-fort-steele-cranbrook/#more-381" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;BC Vacation: Fort Steele and Cranbrook&#8221;</span></a></p>
