<article id="post-336" class="post-336 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains category-travel tag-hiroshima tag-japan tag-miyajima tag-museums tag-shinkansen tag-temples tag-toyohashi">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-hiroshima/" rel="bookmark">Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Hiroshima</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>No hangovers. This was a good way to start the day, even if it was a lot earlier than Jen really would have liked. (Mind you, Jen likes noon as a wake-up time.)<br />
It was warm in the room. The Japanese seem to like it warm. Even trying to turn the heat down didn&#8217;t help. Twenty-four degrees is just uncomfortable. We rose, repacked our bags, and prepared for the trip to Hiroshima. Neither of us were particularly hungry, so would skip breakfast. Chris called to inform us of the paper shinkansen schedule, which we&#8217;d found out about the night before.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-hiroshima/#more-336" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Hiroshima&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-hiroshima/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2004-03-29T16:58:49-07:00">29 March 2004</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/trains/" rel="category tag">Trains</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/hiroshima/" rel="tag">hiroshima</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/japan/" rel="tag">japan</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/miyajima/" rel="tag">miyajima</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/museums/" rel="tag">museums</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/shinkansen/" rel="tag">shinkansen</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/temples/" rel="tag">temples</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/toyohashi/" rel="tag">toyohashi</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-hiroshima/#comments">2 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Hiroshima</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-336 -->

<article id="post-334" class="post-334 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains category-travel tag-irako tag-japan tag-shinkansen tag-tokyo tag-toyohashi tag-yotsukaido">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-toyohashi-irako/" rel="bookmark">Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Toyohashi and Irako</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I slept a little oddly, considering we&#8217;d been up for over 24 hours straight. Woke up once around 3:00 (mostly to go to the bathroom), again at about 5:00, and finally at about 7:50. At that point, it was enough to say I&#8217;d probably adjusted to the time zone.<br />
Jen and I proceeded to get on with our morning. For me, showering and shaving (showering when it&#8217;s eight degrees in the shower room is a bit of an odd experience), gathering our things from the previous night, laying out Chris and Kaz&#8217;s wedding gifts (that they don&#8217;t yet know about), and getting breakfast.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-toyohashi-irako/#more-334" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Toyohashi and Irako&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-toyohashi-irako/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2004-03-27T16:54:59-07:00">27 March 2004</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/trains/" rel="category tag">Trains</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/irako/" rel="tag">irako</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/japan/" rel="tag">japan</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/shinkansen/" rel="tag">shinkansen</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/tokyo/" rel="tag">tokyo</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/toyohashi/" rel="tag">toyohashi</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/yotsukaido/" rel="tag">yotsukaido</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-toyohashi-irako/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Toyohashi and Irako</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
